# Contributing to AI-Dev-discassion

First off, thanks for taking the time to contribute! 🎉

This document provides guidelines for contributing to this repository — a collection of AI-powered development skills, prompts, and automation scripts for Claude Code, GLM, and other LLM coding agents.

## 📦 What We're Building

We aim to create a **practical, battle-tested toolkit** that helps developers (and AI agents) earn bounties, fix bugs, and automate coding tasks. All contributions that improve existing skills or add new ones are welcome.

## 🧭 How Can I Contribute?

### 🐛 Report a Bug / Request a Feature
- Open an [Issue](https://github.com/harrylyu20260808-pixel/AI-Dev-discassion/issues)
- Use the provided templates (bug report / feature request)
- Be clear and include steps to reproduce if applicable

### 💡 Add a New Skill
We welcome new skills! A skill is a `.md` file inside `skills/<skill-name>/SKILL.md` with YAML frontmatter and clear instructions.

**Skill file structure example**:
```markdown
---
name: my-awesome-skill
description: One-line description of what this skill does
---

# My Awesome Skill

## When to Use
- Scenario 1
- Scenario 2

## What This Skill Does
- Action 1
- Action 2

## Usage
Run `/my-awesome-skill` in Claude Code